{"title_page": "Rykhlyanda", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Rykhlyanda\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0420\u044b\u0445\u043b\u044f\u043d\u0434\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Belozersky District, Vologda Oblast|Belozersky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|59|N|37|55|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/belozerskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0437\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Rykhlyanda''' ({{lang-ru|\u0420\u044b\u0445\u043b\u044f\u043d\u0434\u0430}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in [[Belozersky District, Vologda Oblast|Belozersky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 1 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> There is 1 street.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "#REDIRECT [[List of rural localities in Vologda Oblast#Belozersky District]]{{rcat shell|{{R to list entry}}}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "WP:STUB", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rykhlyanda"}
{"title_page": "Arun Kumar (Bihar politician)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Arun Kumar\n| office = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member]] of the [[India Parliament]] <br /> for [[Jahanabad (Lok Sabha constituency)|Jahanabad]]\n| image = Arun Kumar Politician.jpg\n| caption = \n| constituency = \n| successor = \n| footnotes = \n| date = \n| year = \n| source = \n| party = [[ Samata Party (Secular)]]\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1959|10|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place = Maniyawan, [[Jehanabad district|Jehanabad]], [[Bihar]]\n| spouse = Nirmala Kumari\n| children = 1 son, 1 daughter\n| residence = [[Patna]], [[Bihar]]\n| alma_mater = [[Magadh University]] (PHD)\n| website = http://www.drarunkumar.in\n| term_start = 2014\n| term_end = 2019\n1999-2004\n\nMember legislative council Bihar\n1993-1999\n}}\n\n'''Arun Kumar''' is a Member of Parliament in [[India]]. He represents the [[Jahanabad (Lok Sabha constituency)|Jahanabad constituency]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.india.gov.in/my-government/indian-parliament/arun-kumar-0|title=Arun Kumar {{!}} National Portal of India|website=www.india.gov.in|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref> in the [[Lok Sabha]], which is the [[lower house]] of the [[Parliament of India]]. He won the seat in the [[2014 Indian general election]] and 1999, and he is a founding member of the [[Rashtriya Samata Party (Secular)|Samata Party (Secular)]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Constituencywise-All Candidates|url=http://eciresults.nic.in/ConstituencywiseS0436.htm?ac=36|accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref><ref name=\"Satyendra Kumar\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/lok-sabha-elections-2014/news/Contest-between-good-work-and-Narendra-Modi-wave-in-Jehanabad/articleshow/33712825.cms |title=Contest between 'good work' and Narendra Modi wave in Jehanabad |first=Satyendra |last=Kumar |work=The Times of India |date=14 April 2014 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> He is the founder and head of [[Gyan Bharti Model Residential Complex]] school in [[Hisua]], [[Nawada district|Nawada]]. He often visits the school during Annual Day functions as chief guest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/bihar/nawada/news/nitish-modi-join-arun-jaitley-044028-3720702.html|title=\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928 \u0918\u094b\u091f\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0938\u0902\u0932\u093f\u092a\u094d\u0924 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0928\u0940\u0924\u0940\u0936-\u092e\u094b\u0926\u0940: \u0905\u0930\u0941\u0923|last=Automation|first=Bhaskar|date=2019-01-22|website=Dainik Bhaskar|language=hi|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{16th LS members from Bihar}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kumar, Arun}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:16th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Bihar]]\n[[Category:People from Jehanabad district]]\n[[Category:Rashtriya Lok Samata politicians]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Samta Party politicians]]\n\n{{Bihar-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Arun Kumar\n| office = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member]] of the [[India Parliament]] <br /> for [[Jahanabad (Lok Sabha constituency)|Jahanabad]]\n| image = Arun Kumar Politician.jpg\n| caption = \n| constituency = \n| successor = \n| footnotes = \n| date = \n| year = \n| source = \n| party = [[ Samata Party (Secular)]]\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1959|10|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place = Maniyawan, [[Jehanabad district|Jehanabad]], [[Bihar]]\n| spouse = Nirmala Kumari\n| children = 1 son, 1 daughter\n| residence = [[Patna]], [[Bihar]]\n| alma_mater = [[Magadh University]] (PHD)\n| website = http://www.drarunkumar.in\n| term_start = 2014\n| term_end = 2019\n1999-2004\n\nMember legislative council Bihar\n1993-1999\n}}\n\n'''Arun Kumar''' is a Member of Parliament in [[India]]. He represents the [[Jahanabad (Lok Sabha constituency)|Jahanabad constituency]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.india.gov.in/my-government/indian-parliament/arun-kumar-0|title=Arun Kumar {{!}} National Portal of India|website=www.india.gov.in|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref> in the [[Lok Sabha]], which is the [[lower house]] of the [[Parliament of India]]. He won the seat in the [[2014 Indian general election]] and 1999, and he is a founding member of the [[Rashtriya Samata Party (Secular)|Samata Party (Secular)]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Constituencywise-All Candidates|url=http://eciresults.nic.in/ConstituencywiseS0436.htm?ac=36|accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref><ref name=\"Satyendra Kumar\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/lok-sabha-elections-2014/news/Contest-between-good-work-and-Narendra-Modi-wave-in-Jehanabad/articleshow/33712825.cms |title=Contest between 'good work' and Narendra Modi wave in Jehanabad |first=Satyendra |last=Kumar |work=The Times of India |date=14 April 2014 |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> He is the founder and head of [[Gyan Bharti Model Residential Complex]] school in [[Hisua]], [[Nawada district|Nawada]]. He often visits the school during Annual Day functions as chief guest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/bihar/nawada/news/nitish-modi-join-arun-jaitley-044028-3720702.html|title=\u0938\u0943\u091c\u0928 \u0918\u094b\u091f\u093e\u0932\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0938\u0902\u0932\u093f\u092a\u094d\u0924 \u0939\u0948\u0902 \u0928\u0940\u0924\u0940\u0936-\u092e\u094b\u0926\u0940: \u0905\u0930\u0941\u0923|last=Automation|first=Bhaskar|date=2019-01-22|website=Dainik Bhaskar|language=hi|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{16th LS members from Bihar}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kumar, Arun}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:16th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Bihar]]\n[[Category:People from Jehanabad district]]\n[[Category:Rashtriya Lok Samata politicians]]