{"title_page": "2003 Latvian Higher League", "text_new": "The '''[[2003 in football (soccer)|2003 season]]''' in the '''[[Latvian Higher League]]''', named ''[[Virsl\u012bga]]'', was the thirteenth domestic competition since the Baltic nation gained [[independence]] from the [[Soviet Union]] on 6 September 1991. Eight teams competed in this edition, with [[Skonto FC]] claiming the title.\n\n==Final table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n\n|team1=SKO|name_SKO=[[Skonto FC|Skonto]]\n|team2=LIE|name_LIE=[[FK Liep\u0101jas Metalurgs|Liep\u0101jas Metalurgs]]\n|team3=VEN|name_VEN=[[FK Ventspils|Ventspils]]\n|team4=DIN|name_DIN=[[Dinaburg FC|Dinaburg]]\n|team5=R\u012aG|name_R\u012aG=[[FK R\u012bga|R\u012bga]]\n|team6=GAU|name_GAU=[[FK Valmiera|Gauja]]\n|team7=AUD|name_AUD=[[FK Auda/Alberts R\u012bga|Auda/Alberts R\u012bga]]\n|team8=RKB|name_RKB=[[RKB-Arma]]\n|win_SKO=23|draw_SKO=4|loss_SKO=1|gf_SKO=91|ga_SKO=9|status_SKO=C\n|win_LIE=22|draw_LIE=2|loss_LIE=4|gf_LIE=100|ga_LIE=29\n|win_VEN=19|draw_VEN=4|loss_VEN=5|gf_VEN=89|ga_VEN=18\n|win_DIN=13|draw_DIN=5|loss_DIN=10|gf_DIN=43|ga_DIN=36\n|win_R\u012aG=8|draw_R\u012aG=5|loss_R\u012aG=15|gf_R\u012aG=34|ga_R\u012aG=63\n|win_GAU=6|draw_GAU=5|loss_GAU=17|gf_GAU=27|ga_GAU=70\n|win_AUD=4|draw_AUD=1|loss_AUD=23|gf_AUD=21|ga_AUD=88\n|win_RKB=2|draw_RKB=4|loss_RKB=22|gf_RKB=23|ga_RKB=115|status_RKB=R\n\n|col_UCL=green1|text_UCL=Qualification for [[2004\u201305 UEFA Champions League#First qualifying round|Champions League first qualifying round]] \n|result1=UCL\n|col_UC=blue1|text_UC=Qualification for [[2004\u201305 UEFA Cup#First qualifying round|UEFA Cup first qualifying round]] \n|result2=UC|result3=UC\n|col_IC=#ccccff|text_IC=Qualification for [[2004 UEFA Intertoto Cup#First round|Intertoto Cup first round]]\n|result4=IC\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to [[Latvian First League]]\n|result8=R\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Top scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Rank\